osu!mania Speedmapping Challenge
My Maps | My Unsubmitted Maps
Here's info and descriptions for most of my maps
If you want to talk about BN or mapper stuff, please feel free to send me a PM!

Listen to me talk about myself
Full View

News:
- 1/15/17: Become a commentator for MWC 7K 2017
- My third ranked map
- Won second place in the Mania Aspire Contest
- My second ranked map: Renard vs Kitsune² - The Castle
- 31/5/16: Joined the BNG!
- Check out our Undertale collab: toby fox - Your Best Nightmare + Finale
- Wanna see a measure line scroll backwards? Cuprate - Tentacle VIP
- Oops I made a mod queue ;n;
- Had a great time playing in MWC 7k 2016
- Check out my 100th-map request pack: http://vsrg.club/forum/showthread.php?tid=326
- older stuff: idk I didn't have a user page at the time

I'm a mania mapper and taiko/mania player. I started mapping in 2012 on a game called Feel the Beats (which is 100% dead right now), and you can check out my hilariously bad first map here if you'd like. The community was really small and well-connected, so I made a lot of friends <3

I map a lot of piano and Renard songs, and I love jacks, LNs, SVs, and anything expressive. If you want to check out my maps, here are some highlights:

• Vospi - Reverence | my first ranked map. pretty good indicator of my charting style overall
• Marguerite du Pre (arranged by Sin2324) - Marie Antoinette | fun piano map (old tho)
• Renard vs Kitsune^2 - The Castle | one of my best 5ks. cool LN stuff. ranked!
• Culprate - Tentacle VIP | groundbreaking SV map + cool patterns
• Kyle Gann - Bud Ran Back Out | insane piano masterpiece
• Renard - Can't Stop Loving You | hilarious SVs if you're into that kind of thing

Thanks to Sangahlolo and auxy for supporter ;p;
BN status: CLOSED

I think I'll be going inactive soon. Best of luck to anyone going for rank
More info
Open means I will accept almost every request that meets my requirements
Semi-Open means I will only accept exceptional requests.
Closed means I will not accept any large requests, but feel free to ask me for advice or help
I'm only partly active right now, so I'm going to be closed for long periods of time.
Please send requests through site PM or in-game PM.

Requirements:
• osu!mania only
• Any keymode. However, I have limited experience in 4k, so if you need an icon on a high-diff 4k map you will have to ask a different BN.
• Any type of request: mod, BN check, timing, SVs, etc.
• If you want a BN check, make sure you have at least 12 SP and a reasonable amount of mods.
• You may not request a BN check if I have already checked one of your maps in the past month.

I'm a mania mapper and taiko/mania player. I started mapping in 2012 on a game called Feel the Beats (which is 100% dead right now), and you can check out my hilariously bad first map [url=https://www.dropbox.com/s/1qn316ljkpeu4o4/m477zorz%20-%20Mario%27s%20pwned%20Slide.osz?dl=0]here[/url] if you'd like. The community was really small and well-connected, so I made a lot of friends <3

I map a lot of piano and Renard songs, and I love jacks, LNs, SVs, and anything expressive. If you want to check out my maps, here are some highlights:

   • [url=https://osu.ppy.sh/s/203929]Vospi - Reverence[/url] | my first ranked map. pretty good indicator of my charting style overall

   • [url=https://osu.ppy.sh/s/293475]Renard vs Kitsune^2 - The Castle[/url] | one of my best 5ks. cool LN stuff. ranked!

   • [url=https://osu.ppy.sh/s/213648]Kyle Gann - Bud Ran Back Out[/url] | insane piano masterpiece
   • [url=https://osu.ppy.sh/s/312234]Renard - Can't Stop Loving You[/url] | hilarious SVs if you're into that kind of thing
